  "response": "Fixing an iPhone 4 camera can involve several steps, depending on the specific issue:\n\n1. Basic troubleshooting:\n- Restart the phone\n- Clean the camera lens with a soft, lint-free cloth\n- Check for software updates\n- Reset all settings\n\n2. Common hardware issues:\n- If the camera is cracked, you'll need professional repair\n- Check for dust or debris inside the lens\n- Verify camera connections are secure\n\n3. Potential repair options:\n- DIY repair (requires technical skills and special tools)\n- Professional repair at Apple Store or authorized service center\n- Third-party repair shop\n\n4. Specific fixes for common problems:\n- Blurry images: Clean lens, check focus\n- Black screen: Might require camera module replacement\n- Camera not working: Could be software or hardware issue\n\n5. Replacement considerations:\n- Camera module replacement can cost $50-$100\n- Professional repair might be more expensive\n- Consider phone's age and overall condition\n\nNote: Since the iPhone 4 is an older model, finding replacement parts might be challenging. In many cases, it might be more cost-effective to upgrade to a newer device.\n\nIf you're not comfortable with technical repairs, recommend seeking professional assistance.",
